Please, don't try to pursue what is 'trendy' now. Fashion trends are cycling way faster than usual and they're harder to keep up with and be sustainable for longevity of your wardrobe. I'm a year older than you, and as much as I like what some young 'trendy' people are wearing these days, I don't really find it endearing or characteristic of any sort of individuality.. To me, dressing ultra 'trendy' just feels vapid and obnoxious, and it seems like a lot of young people have something to prove in the way they present themselves and go too hard with the way they look. In their attempts at looking unique, I find they are all just looking like part of the same crowd.

I think this style is still fairly relevant anyway, and it holds up. It's just classic vintage attire, stuff you can easily pick up at the thrift and make special and unique to your taste. I wouldn't be wearing the checkerboard vans anymore, but try to find some nice, interesting sneakers that are to your taste. imo, shoes are where personality can make its way into your outfit. a personal choice of shoe makes an outfit really stand out to me, as opposed to a 'trendy' shoe that is getting circulated like crazy (see the sambas, new balances, tiger onitsuka's, all fine shoes but predictable and tells me the wearer is only shopping what influencers tell them to).
